Sentencas: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 (LSN) nanofibers are prepared by electrospinning technique and used as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (CGO) as electrolyte.
Titulo: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 one-dimensional nanofibers as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The as-prepared cathode is highly porous but forms a good contact with the CGO electrolyte after rapid sintering at 900 degrees C for 15 min in air.
Titulo: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 one-dimensional nanofibers as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode performance of LSN nanofibers is measured at various temperatures and under different oxygen partial pressures.
Titulo: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 one-dimensional nanofibers as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two main oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) processes are identified.
Titulo: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 one-dimensional nanofibers as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The rate limiting step for the ORR is the charge transfer process.
Titulo: La1.6Sr0.4NiO4 one-dimensional nanofibers as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
